/* Question: Using MPI point-to-point communication;
 Only the master processor should get the lower and upper limit values for a number range from the user.
 The master must send the lower and upper limit values to the slave processors.
 The relevant number range must be distributed among all processors in the communicator world using a cyclic data distribution method (including upper and lower limits).
 Each processor should use a stopwatch to find how many of the numbers assigned to it are even numbers and determine its execution time for finding those even numbers.
 Slaves must send the count of even numbers they found to the Master.
 The Master must print the total count of even numbers, taking its own processed data into account as well.
 Slaves must send their search operation time to the Master.
 The Master must print the rank and execution time of the processor with the longest search time, including itself.
 Use a sub-function with a bool signature to check if a number is even. 
*/

